Package it.polimi.ingsw.model

Class LineCommonGoal

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.model.CommonGoal
it.polimi.ingsw.model.LineCommonGoal
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class LineCommonGoal extends CommonGoal implements Serializable
LineCommonGoal is a class that represents a generic CommonGoal which is satisfied if the BookShelf contains a given number of lines (rows or columns) each having a given number of different tile type.
Since:
07/04/2023
Version:
2.0
Author:
Tommaso Trabacchin, Melanie Tonarelli, Emanuele Valsecchi, Adem Shehi

    • rule

      public List<EntryPatternGoal> rule(TileType[][] bookShelf)
      The method returns null if the LineCommonGoal is not satisfied for the bookShelf passes as argument. If the LineCommonGoal is satisfied then the method returns the list of the EntryPatternGoal representing the cell in the bookShelf that satisfy the LineCommonGoal.
      Specified by:
      rule in class CommonGoal
      Parameters:
      bookShelf - The bookShelf to check for the goal.
      Returns:
      null if the goal is not satisfied, otherwise the list of the EntryPatternGoal representing the cell in the bookShelf that satisfy the goal.
      See Also:
      • EntryPatternGoal
